full_threads.body:
Hi Heath and team,


Can we please update the Supported Accommodation Enquiries page to have definitions that hover over the funding details?

https://royalrehab.com.au/disability-supports-and-accommodation/supported-accommodation-enquiries/

Below are the funding details:


By hover, I mean something like below where the cursor hovers over a question mark symbol.

Below are the definitions I'd like to be in the hover comments:
Current NDIS plan - Funding through the National Disability Insurance Scheme (NDIS) for people with a disability
SIL in plan - Supported Independent Living funding in NDIS plan.
SDA in plan - Specialist Disability Accommodation (SDA) funding in NDIS plan for participants who require specialist housing solutions.
Other funding body - 24/7 Care - Funding through other insurance Companies eg icare, QBE, Alliance etc
Receiving DSP - Disability Support Pension - Financial help if you have a permanent physical, intellectual or psychiatric condition that stops you from working.
Eligible for Housing Pathways - Housing Pathways is the way applications for housing assistance are managed in NSW.

Any questions, let me know.

Thank you,
Janina
